                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d755">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12–2845: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Robertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-28T14:00:00+07:00"
                            >December 28, 1945—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:14 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2232. According to telegram dated December 26 from Ward, Ining delegates arrived
                    at Tihwa, December 25. (Embtel 2139, December 11 to Dept repeated Moscow.) Ward
                    states delegates’ attitude <pb facs="1035" n="1025" xml:id="pg_1025"/> said to
                    be conciliatory and friendly. (Sent Dept, repeated Moscow.) Chiang Ching-kuo,
                    Generalissimo’s son, was due at Tihwa, December 26 or 27, Ward stated.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
